# General IP ROCEV Example

Use this shape for any IP.

## Case

```text
<ip> / <feature or edge case>
```

## ROCEV map

| ROCEV | General IP example |
|---|---|
| Requirement | `<ip>` must handle `<case>` correctly. |
| Obligation | O1: when `<condition>` occurs, DUT must produce `<expected behavior>`. O2: no unintended side effect occurs. |
| Contract | Expected model/checker defines the result; scoreboard compares RTL observed vs expected; coverage contains `<case>`. |
| Evidence | `rtl/rtl_compile.json`, `lint/dut_lint.json`, `sim/results.xml`, `sim/scoreboard_events.jsonl`, `cov/coverage.json`, `sim/*.vcd`, optional `verify/formal_status.json`. |
| Validation | Closed only if the selected obligation has fresh passing evidence. Formal proof is a separate stronger check, not a substitute for missing stimulus. |

## Bad report

```text
Directed tests passed.
```

Why this is weak:

- It does not say which requirement was checked.
- It does not say which obligation was closed.
- It does not say whether RTL matched the expected model.
- It does not say whether coverage hit the target case.

## Better report

```text
Requirement:
  <ip> must handle <case>.

Obligation:
  O1: when <condition> happens, DUT must produce <expected behavior>.

Contract:
  expected model/checker defines <expected behavior>;
  scoreboard compares RTL observed vs expected;
  coverage includes <case>.

Evidence:
  sim/results.xml PASS
  sim/scoreboard_events.jsonl contains this obligation
  cov/coverage.json shows the target case/bin
  sim/<ip>.vcd exists for debug

Validation:
  closed for O1
```

## Formal note

Formal can add another contract:

```text
Property:
  <bad condition> must never produce <forbidden output/state>

Evidence:
  verify/protocol_assertions.sva
  verify/formal_status.json

Validation:
  closed only for the property and assumptions that were actually proven
```

## Filled-in examples

```text
FIFO:
  Requirement: FIFO preserves order.
  Obligation: the first pushed item is the first popped item.
  Contract: reference queue model + scoreboard compare.
  Evidence: results.xml, scoreboard row, full/empty coverage.
  Validation: closed for order preservation.
```

```text
Register block:
  Requirement: W1C status bits clear only when written with 1.
  Obligation: writing 0 does not clear a status bit.
  Contract: register model/checker defines expected readback.
  Evidence: APB/AHB test, readback scoreboard, coverage bin.
  Validation: closed for W1C zero-write behavior.
```

```text
Packet parser:
  Requirement: invalid header is rejected.
  Obligation: parser must not emit a valid packet for invalid header.
  Contract: expected model says valid_out=0 and drop_reason is observable.
  Evidence: sim result, scoreboard row, invalid-header coverage, optional VCD.
  Validation: closed for that invalid-header case.
```
